d7c88845-af2f-4e5a-8e2f-0c5cf41e0352	Superspace Arch	Info	info@superspacearch.com	NYC Farmy : A Vertical Farming Community	PLANNED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	New York City	United States of America	40.7128	-74.006	NYC Farm Museum is a 6,500 m² vertical farming tower in Manhattan that blends agriculture, housing, and public space into a self-sufficient ecosystem. Located along the High Line on Lenape land, it honors both natural heritage and the city’s evolving urban fabric. Eight-layered fields grow seasonal crops, supported by rooftop wind turbines and rainwater harvesting systems. Public paths, labs, and rooftops foster education, food distribution, and research. By shortening farm-to-table cycles and inviting youth into farming, it promotes climate action and resilient city life.	NYC Farm Museum is a 6,500 m² vertical farming tower in Manhattan that blends agriculture, housing, and public space into a self-sufficient ecosystem. Located along the High Line on Lenape land, it honors both natural heritage and the city’s evolving urban fabric. Eight-layered fields grow seasonal crops, supported by rooftop wind turbines and rainwater harvesting systems. Public paths, labs, and rooftops foster education, food distribution, and research. By shortening farm-to-table cycles and inviting youth into farming, it promotes climate action and resilient city life.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	P17	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
d30a943c-c8a3-4555-abea-ce2cf2e66c35	Superspace Arch	Info	info@superspacearch.com	Weave : Threads of Lines Weaving Lives	PLANNED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	Austin	United States of America	30.2672	-97.7431	Weave is a modular, 3D-printed housing project designed to address the global housing crisis through affordability, sustainability, and community. Originating in the Texas desert, it uses desert sand concrete, green roofs, and passive cooling to create climate-adapted homes. Housing units, or “threads,” cluster into “knots” and “neighborhoods,” balancing privacy and shared spaces. The project integrates water collection, renewable energy, and the Weave Up! app for customization and education. Scalable globally, Weave offers a replicable model for sustainable living, proving that housing can be dignified, efficient, and environmentally responsible.	Weave is a modular, 3D-printed housing project designed to address the global housing crisis through affordability, sustainability, and community. Originating in the Texas desert, it uses desert sand concrete, green roofs, and passive cooling to create climate-adapted homes. Housing units, or “threads,” cluster into “knots” and “neighborhoods,” balancing privacy and shared spaces. The project integrates water collection, renewable energy, and the Weave Up! app for customization and education. Scalable globally, Weave offers a replicable model for sustainable living, proving that housing can be dignified, efficient, and environmentally responsible.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 13:00:00.604992	2026-04-18 13:00:00.604992	P28	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
