001e2be7-08c4-4dae-95bd-1080d35ca460	Re Genera Espacio	Christian Enrique De La Torre Sánchez / Adriana Hernández Sánchez	christian.delatorre@correo.buap.mx	Neighborhood Arts and Crafts Workshop of the Historic Center of Puebla (Taller Barrial de Artes y Oficios del Centro Histórico de Puebla)	IN_PROGRESS	APPROVED	SECTION_V	Puebla	Mexico	19.0413	-98.2062	Since 2013, Re Genera Espacio -a group led by architects- has coordinated Taller Barrial de Artes y Oficios del Centro Histórico de Puebla realizing activities for built heritage conservation (16th-19th centuries) under a sustainable approach. With support of specialists, it implements traditional construction knowledge, techniques, and procedures (masonry, plasterwork, carpentry, pottery, adobe) in vulnerable older barrios (Analco, San Antonio, El Refugio, Santa Anita), with limited financial resources and collaboration of volunteers and neighbors. The initiatives include restoration of church niches and facades of artisan workshops, and the improvement of communal restrooms in vecindades.	Since 2013, Re Genera Espacio -a group led by architects- has coordinated Taller Barrial de Artes y Oficios del Centro Histórico de Puebla realizing activities for built heritage conservation (16th-19th centuries) under a sustainable approach. With support of specialists, it implements traditional construction knowledge, techniques, and procedures (masonry, plasterwork, carpentry, pottery, adobe) in vulnerable older barrios (Analco, San Antonio, El Refugio, Santa Anita), with limited financial resources and collaboration of volunteers and neighbors. The initiatives include restoration of church niches and facades of artisan workshops, and the improvement of communal restrooms in vecindades.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	P79	Christian Enrique De La Torre Sánchez / Adriana Hernández Sánchez	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
04992fb7-226c-4b88-a01b-eaf432811c90	pool Architekten	General contractor Schäfer Holzbautechnik; Construction management Takt Baumanagement; Timber construction engineers Makiol Wiederkehr; Structural engineers Schnetzer Puskas Ingenieure; HVAC (Heating, Ventilation, Air Conditioning) Grünberg + Partner; Ele	entwicklung@poolarch.ch	Temporäre Sportbauten – Zürich	IMPLEMENTED	APPROVED	SECTION_I	Zurich	Switzerland	47.3769	8.5417	In response to urgent school infrastructure needs, Zürich commissioned modular, demountable sports halls built from prefabricated timber. Designed for reuse and multiple relocations, these halls offer full-scale gym facilities for temporary school campuses. The lightweight frame, translucent façade, and visible wooden grid convey a clear, honest structure. Coloured surfaces react to the urban context, giving each building its own local identity. This repeatable typology demonstrates how temporary can still mean high-quality, sustainable, and dignified. The buildings meet demanding energy and reuse standards while supporting inclusion, community health, and climate-conscious building culture.	In response to urgent school infrastructure needs, Zürich commissioned modular, demountable sports halls built from prefabricated timber. Designed for reuse and multiple relocations, these halls offer full-scale gym facilities for temporary school campuses. The lightweight frame, translucent façade, and visible wooden grid convey a clear, honest structure. Coloured surfaces react to the urban context, giving each building its own local identity. This repeatable typology demonstrates how temporary can still mean high-quality, sustainable, and dignified. The buildings meet demanding energy and reuse standards while supporting inclusion, community health, and climate-conscious building culture.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	P84	General contractor Schäfer Holzbautechnik; Construction management Takt