bf9293a0-eb92-48ea-b88d-17439cdd3a4e	Fundo FICA	Unknown	contato@fundofica.org	Housing First: refurbishing existing stock in Sao Paulo to house homeless families	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	São Paulo	Brazil	-23.5505	-46.6333	This house is part of our Housing First Programme, which houses 60 people who were homeless. Rather than building new homes, we purchased and refurbished several units close to where families were living in an informal settlement. This house was at the risk of being demolished and turned into a high-rise building: FICA turned it into a home for 11 people from different generations of the same family. Through changes to the layout, each household has its own unit with a private bathroom and kitchen. The house is accessible for older and disabled people. The furniture, kitchen appliances and construction materials were reused from other locations. A metal roof was added for thermal comfort.	This house is part of our Housing First Programme, which houses 60 people who were homeless. Rather than building new homes, we purchased and refurbished several units close to where families were living in an informal settlement. This house was at the risk of being demolished and turned into a high-rise building: FICA turned it into a home for 11 people from different generations of the same family. Through changes to the layout, each household has its own unit with a private bathroom and kitchen. The house is accessible for older and disabled people. The furniture, kitchen appliances and construction materials were reused from other locations. A metal roof was added for thermal comfort.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 13:00:00.604992	2026-04-18 13:00:00.604992	P37	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
d716c7e4-ae30-48af-a13c-871b098702a4	En-el	Hannah	lsernah@renobo.com.co	The Bronx Creative District – BDC	IN_PROGRESS	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	Bogotá	Colombia	4.6097	-74.0817	TThe Bronx Distrito Creativo is a profound transformation of the heart of Bogotá. A project that reimagines and redefines the old Bronx — a place that was once a symbol of exclusion and suffering — as the new epicenter of creativity, memory, art, and innovation in Colombia.  It is the country’s first induced creative district, led by the Fundación Gilberto Alzate Avendaño (FUGA) in partnership with RenoBo, aiming to turn this territory into a driver of economic, social, and cultural development through the power of cultural and creative industries.  This space seeks to be a vibrant ecosystem where artists, creators, entrepreneurs, educators, and the community converge, equipped with facilities for training, production, circulation, and gathering. From restoring heritage buildings to creating new public spaces, the project not only preserves the memory of an emblematic place for the city but also projects it into the future with an inclusive, sustainable, and productive vision.  More than an urban intervention, Bronx Distrito Creativo is an opportunity for collective rebirth: a territory of care, culture, and collaboration where creativity will be the common language to rebuild bonds, generate opportunities, and strengthen the social fabric of the city center.	TThe Bronx Distrito Creativo is a profound transformation of the heart of Bogotá. A project that reimagines and redefines the old Bronx — a place that was once a symbol of exclusion and suffering — as the new epicenter of creativity, memory, art, and innovation in Colombia.  It is the country’s first induced creative district, led by the Fundación Gilberto Alzate Avendaño (FUGA) in partnership with RenoBo, aiming to turn this territory into a driver of economic, social, and cultural development through the power of cultural and creative industries.  This space seeks to be a vibrant ecosystem where artists, creators, entrepreneurs, educators, and the community converge, equipped with facilities for training, production, circulation, and gathering. From restoring heritage buildings to creating new public spaces, the project not only preserves the memory of an emblematic place for the city but also projects it into the future with an inclusive, sustainable, and productive vision.  More than an urban intervention, Bronx Distrito Creativo is an opportunity for collective rebirth: a territory of care, culture, and collaboration where creativity will be the common language to rebuild bonds, generate opportunities, and strengthen the social fabric of the city center.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	P20	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
