310f6acb-d71f-4a24-8b3d-0c91b5067dc0	Unknown	Weijiayin	weijiayin2@163.com	SINOVAC Tianfu Factory Renovation	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_IV	Beijing	China	39.9042	116.4074	SINOVAC Tianfu factory, located in the southern suburbs of Beijing's Daxing district, was transformed from an existing industrial building. The density of the factory area is relatively high, and there are not many open spaces. Vaccine production is carried out day and night, and the workshop implements a 24-hour work system. All employees dine in a centralized canteen that is open 24/7 in the southeast corner of the factory area. The employees who dine are constantly flowing in the wind and rain.  Taking into account these factors comprehensively, and without causing significant impact on the surrounding production and office areas, a partial light intervention upgrade and renovation will be carried out. By implanting a prefabricated modular devices, a semi outdoor leisure activity area with wind and rain shelter will be provided for employees at the sunken courtyard that leads to the cafeteria, activating the currently somewhat negative spatial gaps.  The basic geometry of the module comes from the spherical shell that symbolizes the cell. In order to "embed" the spherical shell into the remaining space of the linear boundary, a 60 degree equilateral cutting is made on the projection surface of the circular shell to obtain a module prototype. The main structure consists of a stainless steel string column with a diameter of 100mm and a height of 10m, and a stainless steel circular tube arch beam with a span of 15m. The secondary structure is composed of aluminum alloy rectangular section bars spliced by triangular units, covered with ETFE transparent tension film. This prototype can be combined, assembled, and spread in various remaining spaces.  This kind of intervention, as a highly adaptable system, can also play a role in the upgrading and transformation of multiple existing factories of SINOVAC in the future, becoming a spatial clue, an iconic place, a symbol of the brand, and connecting a series of SINOVAC industrial parks scattered around Beijing. Activate the remaining negative space concretely and subtly, creating a friendly and positive space.	SINOVAC Tianfu factory, located in the southern suburbs of Beijing's Daxing district, was transformed from an existing industrial building. The density of the factory area is relatively high, and there are not many open spaces. Vaccine production is carried out day and night, and the workshop implements a 24-hour work system. All employees dine in a centralized canteen that is open 24/7 in the southeast corner of the factory area. The employees who dine are constantly flowing in the wind and rain.  Taking into account these factors comprehensively, and without causing significant impact on the surrounding production and office areas, a partial light intervention upgrade and renovation will be carried out. By implanting a prefabricated modular devices, a semi outdoor leisure activity area with wind and rain shelter will be provided for employees at the sunken courtyard that leads to the cafeteria, activating the currently somewhat negative spatial gaps.  The basic geometry of the module comes from the spherical shell that symbolizes the cell. In order to "embed" the spherical shell into the remaining space of the linear boundary, a 60 degree equilateral cutting is made on the projection surface of the circular shell to obtain a module prototype. The main structure consists of a stainless steel string column with a diameter of 100mm and a height of 10m, and a stainless steel circular tube arch beam with a span of 15m. The secondary structure is composed of aluminum alloy rectangular section bars spliced by triangular units, covered with ETFE transparent tension film. This prototype can be combined, assembled, and spread in various remaining spaces.  This kind of intervention, as a highly adaptable system, can 