s can absorb 1.6 tons of carbon dioxide per cubic meter, and the entire exterior treatment absorbs a total of 20.8 tons of carbon dioxide. Before construction, we compiled a document titled "Tsinghua Sanjiao Zero-Carbon Space Green and Low-Carbon Construction Requirements" to guide the entire process.  Carbon Reduction in Operation--The project incorporates an intelligent energy control system that displays and regulates power allocation in real time. Utilizing a ‘Mechanism Framework + AI’ for in-depth energy savings, it achieves high-precision performance predictions and global optimization, reducing operational energy consumption. The bathrooms are equipped with highly efficient water-saving fixtures, saving over 20% more water than conventional options. Students can enjoy vegetarian cold lunches here as an alternative to food from the gas canteen. The indoor and outdoor study and communication areas maximize the use of natural light and ventilation during transitional seasons, significantly lowering energy consumption. Additionally, the CIM-based campus carbon neutrality diagnostic platform monitors and recommends ways to optimize overall campus carbon emissions.  Carbon Reduction in Education- The Sanjiao Zero-Carbon Space serves as a platform for the university's scientific research, where an interdisciplinary team of educators can test and	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	P97	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
ae1dfc5e-44fe-4937-93c5-028e5bcfb324	Unknown	Lin06	lrx06@126.com	Yulong Snow Mountain Transportation Complex	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_IV	Lijiang	China	26.8721	100.2299	Lijiang is an internationally renowned tourist city with unique landscapes and mysterious Naxi culture. The most important scenic spot in Lijiang is Yulong Snow Mountain, which is visited by more than 6.5 million tourists every year. Yulong Snow Mountain is the spiritual protector of Naxi people in Lijiang. Naxi people have the habit of worship the snow mountain every year. At the same time, the only road leading from the city to Yulong Snow Mountain was seriously blocked and the parking lots on the mountain was insufficient, resulting in poor tourism experience. These problems have damaged the ecology of Yulong Snow Mountain, resulting in the decline of the snow line year by year and the desertification of the plateau meadow around.  The design of this project take into account the needs of Naxi locals and tourists at the same time, so as to protect the cultural and spiritual heritage of ethnic minorities while developing tourism. The newly built electric rail transit provides safe transportation for the Naxi elderly and children who go to Yulong Snow Mountain for worship, so they no longer need a 40-minute bumpy mountain road trip. The rail transit starting station and 600 EV parking spaces in the project provide tourists with an ecological, safe, convenient and efficient way to travel. After this project came into use, Yulong Snow Mountain area can reduce 15,000 tons of carbon emissions every year, eliminating the damage of gasoline vehicles to the snow mountain ecology. In the construction of the project, the pit body of the landfill in the site is repaired and transformed into the moon pool in the front square. In order to improve the desertification of the land, 1734 local trees are planted in the site. The Baisha Town where the project site is located is located near the Yulong Snow Mountain Scenic Area. It is the largest settlement of the minority Naxi people. The town is composed of sloping roofs and courtyards, which carries the belief of the integration and symbiosis of human beings and nature. In order to integrate into the local texture and fit the cultural tradition of the Naxi people, this design abandons the large-scale centralized layout of conventional transportation buildings, and disassembles the building into a complex of 22 courtyards, continuing the local organic complex, and forming a roof contour line that echoes with the one of Yulong Snow Mountain.  The building adopts a skylight suitable for Lijiang 's climatic characteristics and integrates the low-carbon lifestyle of Lijiang 's traditional ' roasted sun '. The building facade adopts the colorful stone deposited by the unique riverbed of Lijiang to form a heat storage wall, which effectively increases the thermal comfort of non-heating buildings. The construction invites Naxi craftsmen to collage traditional walls and traditional paving, promoting the sustainable inheritance of traditional handicrafts. The building group’s main axis is pointing directly to Yulong Snow Mountain, and a series of squares, pools, halls, viewing platforms are set up on or along the axis. It has become special places to appreciate and worship the magnificent momentum of Yulong Snow Mountain. The Naxi elderly people and girls, as well as tourists, can reach these places equally for free, choosing their favorite locations for worship or sightseeing.	Lijiang is an internationally renowned tourist city with unique landscapes and mysterious Naxi culture. The most important scenic spot in Lijiang is Yulong Snow Mountain, which is visited by more than 6.5 million tourists every year. Yulong Snow Mountain is the spiritual protector of Naxi people in Lijiang. Naxi people have the habit of worship the snow mountain every year. At the same time, the only road leading from the city to Yulong Snow Mountain was ser