28ca7e7a-0216-4c7e-84de-3b4a179d61f6	Natureza Urbana	Pedro Lira, Manoela Machado (Team Leaders), Julia Ximenes (Project Leader), Pedro Norberto, Cauê Marins, Luan Neske, Jean Fortes (Team) and Luciana Sagi (Tourism Specialist).	breno@naturezaurbana.net	Masterplan for Sustainable Economic Development Solutions in Umm Al Quwain MPA	PLANNED	APPROVED	SECTION_III	Umm Al Quwain	United Arab Emirates	25.5647	55.5533	Natureza Urbana was responsible for developing a strategic plan for the regulation of ecotourism in one of the country’s last remaining preserved Marine Protected Areas. The plan aims to structure ecotourism activities in the lagoon in a sustainable way, prioritizing the connection between visitors and the natural environment. To achieve this, the project was carried out in successive phases, including territorial diagnosis and analysis, future visioning, use programming, carrying capacity studies, and benchmarking. These efforts culminated in the development of a detailed Masterplan intended to enhance the visitor experience and create a long-term legacy of environmental preservation.	Natureza Urbana was responsible for developing a strategic plan for the regulation of ecotourism in one of the country’s last remaining preserved Marine Protected Areas. The plan aims to structure ecotourism activities in the lagoon in a sustainable way, prioritizing the connection between visitors and the natural environment. To achieve this, the project was carried out in successive phases, including territorial diagnosis and analysis, future visioning, use programming, carrying capacity studies, and benchmarking. These efforts culminated in the development of a detailed Masterplan intended to enhance the visitor experience and create a long-term legacy of environmental preservation.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	P15	Pedro Lira, Manoela Machado (Team Leaders), Julia Ximenes (Project Leader), Pedro Norberto, Cauê Mari