5066c79e-159b-4fc2-a4e1-0171140d8e1f	SuperSpace Architecture	Unknown	info@superspacearch.com	urbanPRADO : connect the dots & keep it wild	PLANNED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_I	Logroño	Spain	42.4641	-2.4489	UrbanPrado addresses rising heat and water scarcity in Logroño by creating interconnected green corridors, plazas, and shaded urban spaces using curvilinear steel modules that support trees, vines, and seating. RootSmart biodegradable pots harvest dew and rainwater, reducing irrigation needs by 90%. Solar panels integrated into the structures supply clean energy, lowering grid dependence. This holistic approach combines sustainable water management, solar power, and vibrant public green spaces to reduce urban heat islands, boost biodiversity, conserve resources, and foster a climate-resilient, livable city environment.	UrbanPrado addresses rising heat and water scarcity in Logroño by creating interconnected green corridors, plazas, and shaded urban spaces using curvilinear steel modules that support trees, vines, and seating. RootSmart biodegradable pots harvest dew and rainwater, reducing irrigation needs by 90%. Solar panels integrated into the structures supply clean energy, lowering grid dependence. This holistic approach combines sustainable water management, solar power, and vibrant public green spaces to reduce urban heat islands, boost biodiversity, conserve resources, and foster a climate-resilient, livable city environment.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	P23	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
