2cd065e7-0f93-4b5a-b93f-0a81bbcca721	Chamber of Architects Turkey (TMMOB Mimarlar Odası)	Sinan Gunay and Nurhayat Oz / SUPERSPACE	info@superspacearch.com	eCone: Electric Fueling Station of the Future	PLANNED	APPROVED	SECTION_V	Toronto	Canada	43.6532	-79.3832	eCone is a visionary modular electric fueling station redefining sustainable travel with circular design principles. Its radial glulam canopy, inspired by the natural cone seed, shelters 22 EVs while walkable solar panels harvest clean energy to power 182 vehicles annually, offsetting 450 tons of CO₂. Built using precision-fabricated, dry-assembled wooden modules, eCone minimizes waste & carbon footprint. Integrated heating panels melt snow & collect over 1 million liters of water yearly to nurture native plants & community spaces like cafés & public amenities. More than a recharge hub, eCone blends architecture, nature, & tech into a resilient social landmark for Canadian highways & beyond.	eCone is a visionary modular electric fueling station redefining sustainable travel with circular design principles. Its radial glulam canopy, inspired by the natural cone seed, shelters 22 EVs while walkable solar panels harvest clean energy to power 182 vehicles annually, offsetting 450 tons of CO₂. Built using precision-fabricated, dry-assembled wooden modules, eCone minimizes waste & carbon footprint. Integrated heating panels melt snow & collect over 1 million liters of water yearly to nurture native plants & community spaces like cafés & public amenities. More than a recharge hub, eCone blends architecture, nature, & tech into a resilient social landmark for Canadian highways & beyond.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	P80	Sinan Gunay and Nurhayat Oz / SUPERSPACE	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
1f2f7143-a5ae-4a65-8e4f-fe07f00b435a	NIVASA	Akhila Ramesh, Meenakshi K, Anitha Mahendra	nivasaworks@gmail.com	Model Anganwadi	IMPLEMENTED	APPROVED	SECTION_IV	Bangalore	India	12.9716	77.5946	A child-centric, modular Anganwadi prototype designed by NIVASA for the Department of Women and Child Development in Karnataka. Anganwadi centers, catering to 0-6 years, are a crucial part of the Integrated Child Development Services program launched by the government of India.   NIVASA is a social venture, working towards enabling humane and dignified living conditions for the under-served, through scientific and systemic design.   NIVASA strongly believes design to be a catalyst for social change. Nivasa employs a people centric design approach involving the users and multiple stakeholders in the decision making process. They encourage workers’ safety and wellbeing during the construction process.   The design approach rigorously assimilates best practices, applying a scientific method that integrates the use of local materials, encourages play-based learning, and ensures adaptability across diverse climates and geographies.  From a design point, this Model Anganwadi offers an inclusive, sensory-rich, and context-responsive approach for early childhood care and education. At 1020 sq.ft., it incorporates play areas, learning zones, and art-integrated walls using local building materials. Roof options (RCC flat, sloping, or tiled) and safety-focused features like rounded edges and accessible handwash areas make it scalable across regions. Adopted as a government prototype, it's currently replicated in multiple districts. From the program point of view, this center also caters to pregnant and lactating women, adolescent girls etc. Services provided include supplementary nutrition, health check-ups, Immunizations, referral services, Pre-school education, nutrition and health education to mothers and care givers.	A child-centric, modular Anganwadi prototype designed by NIVASA for th