1a6a16e9-839e-43cb-9b15-c6507daf5312	A.LEAD architects ltd.	Beh Kiang Hioke, Mok Chi Kin, Alejo Florentino Jr., Zhao Yiyun	christine@aleadarchitect.com	Cha Kwo Ling Promenade: Enhancement Works for Kwun Tong Sewage Pumping Station (Balancing Tank)	IMPLEMENTED	APPROVED	SECTION_IV	Hong Kong	China	22.3193	114.1694	Cha Kwo Ling Promenade project is a visionary initiative that seamlessly integrates functionality, sustainability, and community engagement. Inspired by Kwun Tong’s rich textile history, the project features the architectural concept of a ‘dancing ribbon’, symbolizing both the area’s past and the fluidity of its future.  Formulation of the Project: The project is formulated based on a deep understanding of Kwun Tong’s historical significance and the contemporary needs of its residents. Once a bustling textile hub, Kwun Tong is reimagined as a vibrant, sustainable, and inclusive urban space. The project aims to utilize the existing resources for sewage treatment while providing a multifunctional public space that fosters community interaction and environmental stewardship.  Architectural Design Concept: Central to the architectural design is the ‘dancing ribbon’ concept, manifested through fluid, undulating forms in the landscape and structures. These ribbon-like pathways and structures guide visitors through the space, offering a dynamic and engaging experience. This design reflects the area’s textile heritage and symbolizes the interconnectedness of the community and the environment.  Sustainability and Innovation: Sustainability is at the core of this project. The sewage treatment facilities incorporate advanced technologies to enhance efficiency and reduce environmental impact. The landscaped deck atop the sewage pumping station exemplifies the ‘single site, multiple use’ model, maximizing land use and integrating Blue-Green infrastructure into urban development.  Place-Making Concept: The place-making concept of the Cha Kwo Ling Promenade focuses on creating a vibrant, inclusive, and accessible public space. The promenade serves as a community hub, encourages social interaction, physical activity, and relaxation, fostering a sense of belonging and community pride.   Iconic Play Area in Hong Kong: Since the opening in August 2023, the Cha Kwo Ling Promenade has been welcomed by local residents and tourists. The park features the innovative play equipment, including an eight-meter-tall tree house tower, water play zones, and bouncing play areas. Designed to stimulate children’s imagination and physical activity, it has become a premier destination for families and tourists. Additionally, the promenade fosters community spirit, encouraging residents and visitors to gather, celebrate, and create lasting memories.  In conclusion, the Kwun Tong Sewage Pumping Station project has conclusively demonstrated that by embracing public participation and going the extra mile in the design process, it is possible to collaboratively create a more vibrant and livable community.	Cha Kwo Ling Promenade project is a visionary initiative that seamlessly integrates functionality, sustainability, and community engagement. Inspired by Kwun Tong’s rich textile history, the project features the architectural concept of a ‘dancing ribbon’, symbolizing both the area’s past and the fluidity of its future.  Formulation of the Project: The project is formulated based on a deep understanding of Kwun Tong’s historical significance and the contemporary needs of its residents. Once a bustling textile hub, Kwun Tong is reimagined as a vibrant, sustainable, and inclusive urban space. The project aims to utilize the existing resources for sewage treatment while providing a multifunctional public space that fosters community interaction and environmental stewardship.  Architectural Design Concept: Central to the architectural design is the ‘dancing ribbon’ concept, manifested through fluid, undulating forms in the landscape and structures. These ribbon-l