620fad8a-aeed-4441-b7c4-4e64b43f27a9	Natureza Urbana	Breno	breno@naturezaurbana.net	Córrego do Bispo Linear Park	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	São Paulo	Brazil	-23.5505	-46.6333	The Córrego do Bispo Linear Park, located in the northern region of São Paulo, was developed based on guidelines established by the Municipal Department of Green and Environment. The Main Core features two access points and a central building composed of three volumes connected by metal roofs, housing public restrooms, administrative areas, staff changing rooms, and technical spaces. Bleachers interspersed with planters serve both as gathering areas and retaining structures. The project also includes a rainwater harvesting system for reuse and the redevelopment of the sidewalk linking to the Fazendinha Core, incorporating new equipment and pocket plazas along the way.	The Córrego do Bispo Linear Park, located in the northern region of São Paulo, was developed based on guidelines established by the Municipal Department of Green and Environment. The Main Core features two access points and a central building composed of three volumes connected by metal roofs, housing public restrooms, administrative areas, staff changing rooms, and technical spaces. Bleachers interspersed with planters serve both as gathering areas and retaining structures. The project also includes a rainwater harvesting system for reuse and the redevelopment of the sidewalk linking to the Fazendinha Core, incorporating new equipment and pocket plazas along the way.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	P11	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
e7919a7f-d519-4d6f-ac09-fa67a488600c	Natureza Urbana	Pedro Lira, Manoela Machado (Team Leaders), Camila Sanches (Project Leader), Laís Pimentel, Pedro Norberto, Pedro Borba, Robert Borba, Breno Pilot, Luan Neske, Maria Caterina di Spigna, Júlia Ximenes (Team), BRL, Geonoma, Fredrico Queiroz, Clívia Borba an	breno@naturezaurbana.net	Armando de Holanda Cavalcanti Park	PLANNED	APPROVED	SECTION_V	Cabo de Santo Agostinho	Brazil	-8.2897	-35.0355	The Armando de Holanda Cavalcanti Metropolitan Park (PMAHC) is a key environmental and cultural asset with unique historical and geological features. It marks the final rupture point between the South American and African continents, about 102 million years ago. With exceptional landscape and cultural value, the park attracts many visitors but faces infrastructure challenges. The masterplan focuses on three pillars: Illumination, highlighting natural and built assets such as religious buildings, military ruins, and geological richness; Connection, improving accessibility and fostering contact with nature and water; and Tourism, adding support points, food services, leisure and educational areas, mobility solutions, and a Geopark museum.	The Armando de Holanda Cavalcanti Metropolitan Park (PMAHC) is a key environmental and cultural asset with unique historical and geological features. It marks the final rupture point between the South American and African continents, about 102 million years ago. With exceptional landscape and cultural value, the park attracts many visitors but faces infrastructure challenges. The masterplan focuses on three pillars: Illumination, highlighting natural and built assets such as religious buildings, military ruins, and geological richness; Connection, improving accessibility and fostering contact with nature and water; and Tourism, adding support points, food services, leisure and educational areas, mobility solutions, and a Geopark museum.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	2026-04-18 12:59:53.078529	P8	Pedro Lira, Manoela Machado (Team Leaders), Camila Sanches (Project Leader), Laís Pimentel, Pedro Norberto, Pedro Borba, Robert Borba, Breno Pilot, Luan Neske, Maria Caterina di Spigna, Júlia Ximenes (Team), BRL, Geonoma, Fredrico Queiroz, Clívia Borba and Daniel Figueiredo (Partnerships).	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
ae8e0d8e-ecff-46c4-9f1c-80cbabf53249	DUARQUI SRL	Arq EFRAIN MIGUEL CALLE SARZURI	alejandro.gaona.mx@gmail.com	Pavilion for the Development of Artistic Skills in Highly Marginalized Areas	PLANNED	APPROVED	SECTION_V	Xalapa	Mexico	19.5438	-96.9269	To address the needs of providing artistic and other cultural expressions in highly marginalized neighborhoods or settlements (preferably rural) within the municipality of Xalapa, replicable to other municipalities in the State of Veracruz. They can also support existing facilities, such as community centers  In order to serve the population of the priority attention areas of the Municipality of Xalapa, where segregation problems are evident and a high rate of urban and social backwardness, inequality, poor accessibility, mobility problems, deficient urban infrastructure and facilities are evident, which together hinder the exercise of the Right to the City of People; reference is made to the guidelines of the Urban Improvement Program (PMU) through which SEDATU promotes the attention to the needs of people by developing comprehensive urban improvement interventions whose objective is to make cities and human settlements inclusive, safe, resilient and sustainable. In accordance with the above, and in synergy with the public policies of the municipal government, urban equipment, public space, mobility, and connectivity works will be carried out:  ◗ Ensure access for all people to adequate, safe, and affordable housing and basic services, as well as improve slums. ◗ Increase inclusive and sustainable urbanization and capacity for participatory, integrated, and sustainable planning and management of human settlements. ◗ Provide universal access to safe, inclusive, and accessible green areas and public spaces, particularly for women and children, older persons, and persons with disabilities. ◗ Promote equality between women and men in all spheres of life; ensure that budget planning incorporates a gender perspective, supports mainstreaming, and provides for the implementation of programs, projects, and actions for equality between women and men; and promote equal access to and the full enjoyment of social rights for women and men. ◗ Implement public policies, programs, and actions aimed at reducing risk factors that contribute to the generation of violence, gender-based violence, and crime, as well as combating the various causes and factors that generate it. Contribute to providing people with protection in the areas of freedom, security, and justice, based on precise, clear, and measurable objectives. ◗ Support positive economic, social, and environmental links between urban, peri-urban, and rural areas by strengthening national and regional development planning and ultimately substantially increasing the number of cities and human settlements that adopt and implement integrated policies and plans to promote inclusion, efficient use of resources, climate change mitigation and adaptation, and disaster resilience. ◗ Reduce the physical and social gap in the implementation of urban public policies, impacting an improvement in the quality of life and comprehensive development of people who exercise their right to the city.	To address the needs of providing artistic and other cultural expressions in highly marginalized neighborhoods or settlements (preferably rural) within the municipality of Xalapa, replicable to other municipalities in the State of Veracruz. They can also support existing facilities, such as community centers  In order to serve the population of the priority attention areas of the Municipality of Xalapa, where segregation problems are evident and a high rate of urban and social backwardness, inequality, poor accessibility, mobility problems, deficient urban infrastructure and facilities are evident, which together hinder the exercise of the Right to the City of People; reference is made to the guidelines of the Urban Improvement Program (PMU) through which SEDATU promotes th