d59a6ec6-853d-441b-bab4-63b9142ecc34	Prefeitura Municipal de Sobral	Yvo Gabriel Sousa Galvão	yvogalvao@sobral.ce.gov.br	Sumaré Square Pilot Project	IMPLEMENTED	APPROVED	SECTION_V	Sobral	Brazil	-3.670293	-40.314005	Developed to bring more ludicity and solve traffic and mobility problems around the neighborhood's Early Childhood Education Center, the Sumaré Square Pilot Project uses tactical urbanism to propose the requalification of it's area through children perspective.	Developed in partnership with Urban95, from children perspective, in an intersectoral way, the Sumaré Square Pilot Project, creates more playful areas tactical urbanism as a means to solve traffic and mobility problems around the neighborhood's Early Childhood Education Center, had the requalification of its small square by proposing expansion through painting, installation of beacons and recreational equipment indicated as a demand by the children of the neighborhood.	Besides improving mobility around the Early Childhood Education Center in the neighborhood and renewing the square located immediately in front of it, the Sumaré Square Pilot Project had the effective participation of the children and other users of the space based on listening methodologies developed in partnership with Urban95 in order to outline guidelines, supporting project decisions and working on the feeling of belonging between the population and the intervention.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF43	José Filizola de Abreu Neto; Igor Fernandes Nóbrega; Ana Lívia Ferreira da Costa; Alana Figueiredo Pontes; Yvo Gabriel Sousa Galvão; Marília Gouveia Ferreira Lima.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
63e4f28b-ba7e-4efc-9e48-404c950a94c5	Ubuntu Arquitetura	Vitor Daher	daher.arquitetura@gmail.com	Park Dom Pedro Requalification	IMPLEMENTED	APPROVED	SECTION_V	São Paulo	Brazil	-23.543931	-46.631567	Led by the Forbes Under 30 entrepreneur Vitor Daher, the Dom Pedro Park Requalification is a reference in how to create a positive, innovative and sustainable partnership between companies, government and citizens.	Muda Social is a third-sector initiative that combines architecture, urban planning, and marketing, allowing Private Companies to invest in Public Spaces, offering free educational activities to implement the 2030 New Urban Agenda into cities, favelas, and other human settlements, making them more inclusive, safe, resilient and sustainable.\r\n\r\nThe requalification of Dom Pedro Park allowed us to transform an area with the worst violence, security, and human rights statistics into an innovative and intelligent territory that serves 1.5 million people daily.	1,4,5, 8, 10, 12: Free educational programming, taught by male and female teachers with equal pay, focusing on entrepreneurship development with social impact.\r\n\r\n2,3,6,13,14,15: Implementation of native and productive landscaping, focusing on the regeneration of local fauna on land, water and air.\r\n\r\n7: Solar energy powering the equipment and activities mentioned above.\r\n\r\n9,11,16,17: Creation of ESG projects tailored to each sponsor, creating a territory that offers benefits to all agents of society: Population, government and private initiative.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	LDP58	Vitor Daher, André Teixeira, Alex Tessitore, Lili Silva, Gabriel Luqui, Gabriela Russo	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
8f840840-f7c6-4567-82e0-7eff8737a591	PPD&I -Partnership for Research, Development and Innovation: Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais - UFMG (University), Instituto Federal de Minas Gerais -IFMG (University) and VLI (Enterprise).	Tiago Nogueira	mapasufmg@gmail.com	MAPAS - Mapping, Analysis,  Prognosis and  Actions for Sustainability	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	Belo Horizonte	Brazil	-19.918219	-43.938831	MAPAS Project is an Partnership for Research which develops innovative socio-environmental solutions for the historical occurrence of risky occupations in the railways right-of-way in Brazil.	MAPAS Project develops innovative solutions to the occurrence of risky irregular occupations in the railway right-of-way operated by the partner cargo transportation concessionaire. For that, management and territorial occupation solutions are being developed to reduce operational insecurity for people, risks to assets and cargo, improving the use of residual areas in railway domain range and preserving social, environmental and economic values shared by the territory and its actors.	The methodology comes from the integration between mapping and territorial data, analysis, development of proposals and elaboration of a Generalizable Territorial Solutions Catalog. A catalog composed by associable parameters, that simulates the constraints of the analyzed area and provide architectural intervention possibilities, which are integrated with the UN Sustainable Development Goals. The partnership's unserviceable materials and their recycling potential or reuse are also applied.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF21	Flávio Agostini, Luciana Bragança, Rejane Magiag Loura, Sarah Dapieve, Tiago Nogueira, Natacha Rena, Ana Isabel de Sá	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
aa32ff54-798f-407d-9d36-84972530d3f9	Mercia Andrade Viana Dutra	Mercia Andrade Viana Dutra	mavddias@gmail.com	Your Kind Home	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	Natal	Brazil	-5.800832	-35.225822	A place can make you happy;\r\nA place can make you emotional;\r\nA place can give you peace;\r\nA place can heal;\r\nA place can enhance wellbeing;\r\nYour place can do all that.\r\n\r\nImprove the quality of your life through your spaces. Your home, your workspace, your educational space, your healing space. And make life-long and significant changes.\r\n\r\n“Your Kind Home” is an online school where specialized professionals work with consulting and classes to assess important needs in people's everyday built environments. Making the space less toxic and more friendly to the users and the environment, a healthier and happier place. By being an online school, people from all over the world can be reached and helped.\r\n\r\nThe classes are meant to include all people, especially those who do not have easy access to specialized professionals like designers and architects. A specific focus on those at risk of exclusion, persons with disabilities, with illness, the needs of children and the elderly. The students, from their own home can begin to promote well-being and start building healthy and prosperous societies step by step.\r\nClasses and consultancies can range from improving hygiene, improving indoor air quality, sick building syndrome, how to have a better layout for a good indoor flow. Learn more about important health factors in a building, for example light, acoustics, air quality, and toxins from buildings and environments.\r\n\r\nThe healthiest and best place we have is our home. \r\nWe are all connected in the same energy, from inside to outside, from our environment to our mind, all relationships are connected. To bring them together, respect each one of them and balance them in our lives is key for healthy relationships and a healthy environment. \r\nA healthy being is connected to a healthy space, to a healthy environment.	“Your Kind Home” is an online school where specialized professionals work with consulting and classes to assess important needs in people's everyday built environments. Making the space less toxic and more friendly to the users and the environment, a healthier and happier place. By being an online school, people from all over the world can be reached and helped.\r\n\r\nThe classes are meant to include all people, especially those who do not have easy access to specialized professionals like designers and architects. A specific focus on those at risk of exclusion, persons with disabilities, with illness, the needs of children and the elderly. The students, from their own home can begin to promote well-being and start building healthy and prosperous societies step by step.\r\nClasses and consultancies can range from improving hygiene, improving indoor air quality, sick building syndrome, how to have a better layout for a good indoor flow. Learn more about important health factors in a building, for example light, acoustics, air quality, and toxins from buildings and environments.\r\n\r\nThe “Kind Architecture” Concept is to create a balance among: \r\nThe Universal Home – Our natural environment and all living things; \r\nThe Inner Home – Your true person;\r\nAnd The Kind Home – Our best built environment.\r\nA balance that will work as a partnership.\r\n\r\nWhen we educate, we create and invest in not only our future, but the community’s as well. Acting directly with the end users we interact and promote a more sustainable future and we can reach each person and their built environments, but also their connections, a “drop in the ocean” partnership. The private sector and civil society having a shared vision and values, working together for a more sustainable future. From local to global, working and learning together.	The “Kind Architecture” Concept is to create a balance among: \r\nThe Universal Home – Our natural environment and all living things; \r\nThe Inner Home – Your true person;\r\nAnd The Kind Home – Our best built environment.\r\nA balance that will work as a partnership.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe are the link between the discoveries in architecture and living in built environments and the end users. We communicate the benefits in the social, environmental and health that come with a better built environment. Architects and designers will be able to contribute by sharing knowledge, collaborating with other specialized professionals to promote in people's everyday home more sustainable solutions.\r\n\r\n\r\nImprove aspects related to comfort, health and well-being of a home through design, classes, consults and coaching, and encourage the involvement of civil society in the efficient use of natural resources, circular economy and social responsibility. \r\nThe end users will be more conscious of their choices, from what to look for when buying bed sheets to a future home. Students will learn about their climate, culture and resources and share what they have learned with others. What will make them happier, what will bring them a healthier lifestyle?\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen we educate, we create and invest in not only our future, but the community’s as well. Acting directly with the end users we interact and promote a more sustainable future and we can reach each person and their built environments, but also their connections, a “drop in the ocean” partnership. The private sector and civil society having a shared vision and values, working together for a more sustainable future. From local to global, working and learning together.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF26	Mercia Andrade Viana Dutra	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
f4bc06a7-0a2b-4d5a-9f63-0b088a4800e2	BVO ARQUITECTOS	Gustavo Vera Ocampo	veraocampo@me.com	FIREFLY PROJECT learning about energy efficiency	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	Montevideo	Uruguay	-34.894443	-56.173933	Flashforward concept: a firefly project, a maximum of light with a minimum waste of resources. The Firefly Pavilion is an experimental model space, temporary icon and center for learning sustainable architecture.	The project is integrated at Montevideo’s waterfront, the city's balcony towards the sea.\r\nA contemporary architecture able to remix in an ecological way the urban and environmental contexts promoting a wide community consciousness beyond its own ephemeral existence.\r\nEnergy efficiency: to prove that is possible to build in a more efficient way if all environmental conditions are considered; topographical, climatic, semantic, functional and technological; to develop an idea that takes advantage of them.	RIGHT TO THE CITY\r\nThe building is inserted into the public promenade RAMBLA, a place for the expression of all citizens, and a site for the exchange of collective experiences.\r\nThe tower intends to continue and reaffirm this dialogue of social, cultural and urban integration, restoring Gasometer 5, part of the industrial heritage of the late 19th-century city. \r\nAn emblematic space within the city, it accommodates a variety of typologies as it takes into account economic and administrative constraints, within a neighborhood that has an identity and a history of its own. The Sur and Palermo neighborhoods are known as the cradle of the Afro-Uruguayan culture. a major contribution to the establishment of a sense of belonging.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF32	Gustavo Vera Ocampo, Martín Boga, Pedro Berger, Julia Pereda, César Reisch, Carla Ribas	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
96b5b170-c465-478e-9a2d-be9d04ed30dc	International Associate AIA, PhD Candidate University of Calgary, AB, Canada	Kulsum Fatima	kulsum.fatima@ucalgary.ca	Building Better from LEED to Living water systems for SDG6	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	Calgary	Canada	51.048735	-114.072474	Connecting UN SDG6 to other UN SDGs	Prepare a narrative using exemplary building examples built in last ten years in North America that emphasize on transition from LEED certified to LBC certified building water systems. This narrative will highlight the role of design interventions in achieving SDG6 and its role in influencing social and physical environments. Additionally, this intend to explore the connections between SDG6 and other SDGs achieved because of SDG6. As a result, it will outline the role of design interventions in establishing these connections and offer a unique perspective for knowledge dissemination around good design practices to achieve SDG6.	UN SDG6 is the central theme for this idea. The building design interventions covered are specific to the achievement of UN SDG goal 6, and connects with the achievement of UN SDG 11, 12, and 13,  and shares value with UN SDG 3, 4, 9 and 16.  In doing so, this idea will transform water design elements into opportunities for user engagement, and empowerment, that promotes UN SDG 6 applications and can be replicated as a set of good practice at locations motivated to incorporate similar water sustainability innovations.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF36	Kulsum Fatima	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
