355d12b8-775a-4abf-ae0e-f4b416864aed	Casa Cidade Arquitetura e Urbanismo	Renata Fragoso Coradin	renata.coradin@casacidade.com.br	Guaicuri: Social Urbanism	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	São Paulo	Brazil	-23.543931	-46.631567	The Guaicuri Project implies on the requalification of public areas into a new, green, front with leisure and preservation cores along the Guaicuri canal, articulating mixed-use social housing complexes	Access to qualified housing, education, health, sanitary conditions, and quality leisure spaces are premises of the Guaicuri social urbanism project, proposed for an area approximately of 87.000m² in the extreme south of the city of São Paulo. It proposes a linear park along the canal where new and existing dwellings compose open leisure spaces, in addition of institutional uses with a new nursery and new health unit, as well as commercial spaces on the ground floor of the buildings.	The urbanization and provision of new social housing units in the Guaicuri area is one of the solutions to a social vulnerability context, where residents now live in precarious houses above a polluted stream. The main goal of the project is to combine public green areas, adequate and accessible housing, commercial and institutional spaces to promote coexistence, equity and well-being. It mainly contributes to the first objective of sustainable development goals, “no poverty”.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF54	Renata Fragoso Coradin; Amanda Ramos Silva Santos; Ana Paula Coelho; Caroline de Souza Moura; Felipe Maike Lima de Souza Oliveira; Giovanna Sambugaro; Gustavo Bento Silva; Ian dos Santos Araújo; Juliana Bizzi Radi de Ponti; Juliana Nunes Watanabe; Letícia Ferreira; Matheus de Vasconcelos Casimiro; Soraya Mayumi Tamate Palmeira de Paula; Suellen Cristina Pivato; Alexandre Horiye Ferreira; Daniela Arduino Dezidera Horiye; Joice Lopes; Elisabete França; Ana Clara Gurgel; Fernanda Souza Silva; Maria Teresa Cardoso Fedeli; Mayra Rodrigues; Vanessa Padiá de Souza	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
42056799-3d63-41f8-9b45-1acf6a3f32ea	Faculty of Public Health at USP	Isabel Ammann Saad	isabelsaad8@gmail.com	Bioremediation and waste management combined with the recovery of canalized urban streams: Project proposal in the Jaguaré stream	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	São Paulo	Brazil	-23.543931	-46.631567	Return the curves and the margins of the channeled urban river with a floating structure where macrophyte plants are trapped that help in cleaning the water via Bioremediation, combined with the management of floating waste.	This project aims at the sustainable treatment of water from channeled rivers and the removal of surface residues from the Jaguaré stream in Sao Paulo. Aiming to increase the quality of life in the surroundings and the environmental quality of the floodplains that were reduced for the implementation of roads. It is a design proposal for floating structures on the Jaguaré Stream that simulate the meandering floodplains characteristic of the rivers of the Alto Tietê Basin, in an allusion to the curves that no longer exist.	From the point of view of sustainability and resilience, the project is an action to clean polluted water and minimize the waste that reaches the oceans. The project also elaborates forms of explanatory awareness for the local communities. The actions contemplated here are in line with Sustainable Development Goals number 3, as it encourages the cleaning of water that may contain disease vectors. SDG 4 with regard to environmental education actions for the population. SDG number 6 as it is a water treatment that contains sewage and diffuse pollution. And SDG 15 that indicates resilience and sustainability within the city and its channeled rivers.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF57	Isabel Ammann Saad	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
