58a60bf5-0e00-47da-be2e-91f63b34cfd3	categoria impossível	lucas radatz	email@categoriaimpossivel.site	spatial sublimation as an alternative to fragmentary drives	IMPLEMENTED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	São Paulo	Brazil	-23.543931	-46.631567	The urban-regional of the future lies in the understanding of the counterposition of anthropic and natural dispersion and fragmentation, based on new ways of dealing with the urban in the 21st century. An alternative experimentation merging superpositions and transversalities to the scope of planning projects and urban-architectural design.	According to Walter Benjamin's reflections about the cities of modernity, the urban space makes the human psyche tangible, reverberating in its social organization, compositional structure, and mode of occupation. The urban-regional project understands as problematic the counterposition of dispersion and fragmentation, anthropic and natural, basing itself on new forms in the 21st century. In an alternative experimentation to the highly complex issues brought by such debate, this project merges superpositions and transversalities to the projects' scope.	It is proposed to deal with the spatial construction crossing scales, from plan to project, in which the multiscale fragmentation of nature, the collective and individuals may result in an urban and contemporary totality and simultaneity. While the condition of heterogeneous elements no longer exists in isolation, composing spaces in which the limitations and normalities are dissolved, joining the systemic elements that configure the mosaic of the landscape.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF64	Lucas Radatz	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
