e62c090f-d430-4fe7-b64e-43970f8c736d	Karen Kubey	Karen	karen@karenkubey.net	Aging Against the Machine	PLANNED	SUBMITTED	SECTION_V	Oakland	United States of America	37.8044	-122.2712	Aging is not a problem to be solved. The problem is the range of barriers—spatial, social, financial, and cultural—that make it difficult to grow older with dignity and in community. Older people in the United States are often either isolated at home or subjected to institutionalized, expensive forms of care. This project presents alternative housing and community development scenarios for aging in place in the culturally and racially diverse neighborhood of West Oakland, California. Speculative designs—ranging from interior home renovations to collective land ownership models to new green infrastructure—integrate with social programs to contribute to a community-based approach to aging.	Aging is not a problem to be solved. The problem is the range of barriers—spatial, social, financial, and cultural—that make it difficult to grow older with dignity and in community. Older people in the United States are often either isolated at home or subjected to institutionalized, expensive forms of care. This project presents alternative housing and community development scenarios for aging in place in the culturally and racially diverse neighborhood of West Oakland, California. Speculative designs—ranging from interior home renovations to collective land ownership models to new green infrastructure—integrate with social programs to contribute to a community-based approach to aging.	See detailed description	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	2026-04-18 13:00:15.086189	P77	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
