0baf75d8-2203-4b2a-9ba9-2918a17309b2	MH Architects	Mohamed Hendawi	info@mharchitects-eg.com	Child Development Center	IMPLEMENTED	APPROVED	SECTION_III	Cairo	Egypt	30.046784	31.239582	A Biophilic Child Development Center designed by Architect Mohamed Hendawi, P.H. D founder of MH Architects based in Cairo, Egypt. Project Location is MASQUT, Oman. Land Area is 15900 m2. BUA is 7000 m2. The center is G+4.	The main objective Is to create a place and spaces that play a vital role in the healing and recovery process based on the scientific proven knowledge and Human’s well-being needs. In this designed Livable Project, Architect Mohamed Hendawi, mainly used the BIOPHILIC Design Concept and its fourteen patterns. Designer created Shaded Cooled Echo Garden full of different activities for the kids and their families to enjoy the direct interaction with the NATURE even in the very hot and humidity period, which is not more than 3 months a year. MH had considered and applied the following design principles in OMAN’s Child Development Center:\r\n\r\n•\tWe brought Nature inside the Built Environment\r\n•\tWe Reconnected Humans with their Native Nature\r\n•\tWe used Nature analogs in our structure elements.\r\n•\tWe used Natural Materials for Façade Cladding\r\n•\tWe increased the Mount of Vegetation\r\n•\tWe increased the amount of Water ponds\r\n•\tWe increased the amount of Living-things\r\n•\tBring vegetation to each level\r\n •\tCreating Green Roofs in different levels.\r\n•\tOne total floor area “The Shaded ECO GARDEN”\r\n The design was created based on the following equation\r\n\r\nHuman + Ecology + Science + culture + Art + Design	The Biophilic Child Development Center design is based on integrating Nature with the built environment to create spaces and places that positively impact the human brain and physical condition. The designer used a high level of vegetation, green roofs, and single-loaded building with sun breakers to create a healthy, livable, and low energy consumption built environment. Oman is hot country, thus, designer created an Eco shaded/cooled garden to allow the users to be integrated with NATURE all the year long which fasten the recovery process. Nature has it all.	\N	\N	\N	\N	t	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	2026-03-01 19:41:05.683573	IFF5	Mohamed Hendawi	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
534f9054-ea57-43ed-9311-d472c61c0e0f	Unknown	Unknown	mukaratirwa@yahoo.com	New City in Mt. Hampden	IN_PROGRESS	SUBMITTED	SECTION_III	Harare	Zimbabwe	-17.8252	31.0335	THE NEW CITY IN MT. HAMPDEN, ZIMBABWE- SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT GOAL N0.11  BACKGROUND In October 2019, Government of Zimbabwe commissioned the University of Zimbabwe to come up with a master plan for the New City in Mt. Hampden after Cabinet had approved the “Smart City” concept of the New City designed by Architect Mukaratirwa in December 2018.  THE SITE IN RELATION TO MT. HAMPDEN Mt. Hampden is twenty (20) kilometers from Harare City Center along the Old Mazowe Road. It is a natural landmark, seventy (70) meters higher than the surrounding area and has a magnificent panoramic view of the surroundings.   GENERAL The proposed project will see the development of about 15,000 hectares of land into a New City with the New Parliament Building as the focal point and catalyst for this new development.   The urban development and construction of the New City in Mt. Hampden would conform to the sustainable development strategy with the integration/coordination between the economy, society, population, resource and the environment; while strengthening the urban function of an international metropolis with a prosperous economy, civilized society and beautiful environment as well as an international economic, financial, trade and industrial center.  OVERRAL VISION OF THE NEW CITY The overall vision for The New City is “to be an efficient and ‘intelligent’ and “smart” city, developed within the context of a sustainable garden city concept that would provide comfort and security for its inhabitants well into the 22nd century”.   SPATIAL PLANNING VISIONING STRATEGY The design embodies a spatial structure with “multiple axes and multiple cores” with a comprehensive transportation system of two networks: air and ground, with ground network of roads, railways coordinated through the integration of physical infrastructure with digital infrastructure, information technology and operational technology thus achieving “smart mobility”.  ENVIRONMENTAL PLANNING VISIONING STRATEGY  The New City in Mt. Hampden would be a Smart and Sustainable City that will meet the needs of both present and future generations while protecting the environment and heritage, and responding to risks and opportunities associated with global environmental changes.The New City in Mt. Hampden will be a “Smart Green” City that will preserve pristine forests with rich biological diversity and maintain vegetation corridors to protect the ecologically functioning of the environment and attract tourists.   It will preserve wetlands and consider them as natural infrastructure for nature conservation, landscape planning and water resources management;   The New City in Mt. Hampden will be A New African City that will have the amenities of a smart city with distinct African and Zimbabwean flavour that is drawn from the country’s colourful history. It should embrace its environment, heritage and landscape and uses that heritage as a leverage for development and quality living; • Envision the city to have: • A name that is drawn from its heritage; • Heritage parks with archaeological, historical, natural heritage preserved in situ; • Vibrant heritage tourism; archaeological/historical; farming, mining; colonial heritage attractions;   NEW CITY ARCHITECTURE VISIONING  INTRODUCTION  We would like to think that a century from now people would know they are in the New City in Mt. Hampden because of the uniqueness of the city architecturally where they should experience “The art of architectural and engineering efficiency and usefulness”.   IMAGERY  The increasing use of traditional forms as a source of contemporary design will be widely used in the New City in Mt. Hampden, gaining momentum particularly in the the face of a self-indulgent architecture of post-modernism and the reductive universality of modern architecture.   WATER FEATURES  Water, the ancestral cradle and the primordial sustenance of all life forms, will play an important role in traditional architecture and urban planning in the New City. An essential component of the landscape, it will receive prominent treatment in gardens as an experiential and reflective element.   THE GARDEN  “The construction and enjoyment of a garden accustoms people to beauty, to its instinctive use, even to its pursuit.” - Luis Barragán.   In the New City, gardens will be created out of a mixture of extremely sensitivity for plants and an expressed desire to complement buildings as well as invoke different moods at different times of the day. A sense of place and primordial presence will be strongly elicited.	THE NEW CITY IN MT. HAMPDEN, ZIMBABWE- SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT GOAL N0.11  BACKGROUND In October 2019, Government of Zimbabwe commissioned the University of Zimbabwe to come up with a master plan for the New City in Mt. Hampden after Cabinet had approved the “Smart City” concept of the New City designed by Architect Mukaratirwa in December 2018.  THE SITE IN RELATION TO MT. HAMPDEN Mt. Hampden is twenty (20) kilometers from Harare City Center along the Old Mazowe Road. It is a natural landmark, seventy (70) meters higher than the surrounding area and has a magnificent panoramic view of the surroundings.   GENERAL The proposed project will see the development of about 15,000 hectares of land into a New City with the New Parliament Building as the focal point and catalyst for this new development.   The urban development and construction of the New City in Mt. Hampden would conform to the sustainable development strategy with the integration/coordination between the economy, society, population, resource and the environment; while strengthening the urban function of an international metropolis with a prosperous economy, civilized society and beautiful environment as well as an international economic, financial, trade and industrial center.  O